19#include <sys/types.h>
20
21#include <stdlib.h>
22#include <time.h>
23
24#include "tmux.h"
25
26/*
27 * Displays a message in the status line.
28 */
29
30#define DISPLAY_MESSAGE_TEMPLATE \
31 "[#{session_name}] #{window_index}:" \
32 "#{window_name}, current pane #{pane_index} " \
33 "- (%H:%M %d-%b-%y)"
34
35static enum cmd_retval cmd_display_message_exec(struct cmd *,
36 struct cmdq_item *);
37
38const struct cmd_entry cmd_display_message_entry = {
39 .name = "display-message",
40 .alias = "display",
41
42 .args = { "c:pt:F:", 0, 1 },
43 .usage = "[-p] [-c target-client] [-F format] "
44 CMD_TARGET_PANE_USAGE " [message]",
45
46 .target = { 't', CMD_FIND_PANE, 0 },
47
48 .flags = CMD_AFTERHOOK,
49 .exec = cmd_display_message_exec
50};
51
52static enum cmd_retval
53cmd_display_message_exec(struct cmd *self, struct cmdq_item *item)
54{
55 struct args *args = self->args;
56 struct client *c, *target_c;
57 struct session *s = item->target.s;
58 struct winlink *wl = item->target.wl;
59 struct window_pane *wp = item->target.wp;
60 const char *template;
61 char *msg;
62 struct format_tree *ft;
63
64 if (args_has(args, 'F') && args->argc != 0) {
65 cmdq_error(item, "only one of -F or argument must be given");
66 return (CMD_RETURN_ERROR);
67 }
68
69 template = args_get(args, 'F');
70 if (args->argc != 0)
71 template = args->argv[0];
72 if (template == NULL)
73 template = DISPLAY_MESSAGE_TEMPLATE;
74
75 /*
76 * -c is intended to be the client where the message should be
77 * displayed if -p is not given. But it makes sense to use it for the
78 * formats too, assuming it matches the session. If it doesn't, use the
79 * best client for the session.
80 */
81 c = cmd_find_client(item, args_get(args, 'c'), 1);
82 if (c != NULL && c->session == s)
83 target_c = c;
84 else
85 target_c = cmd_find_best_client(s);
86 ft = format_create(item->client, item, FORMAT_NONE, 0);
87 format_defaults(ft, target_c, s, wl, wp);
88
89 msg = format_expand_time(ft, template, time(NULL));
90 if (args_has(self->args, 'p'))
91 cmdq_print(item, "%s", msg);
92 else if (c != NULL)
93 status_message_set(c, "%s", msg);
94 free(msg);
95
96 format_free(ft);
97
98 return (CMD_RETURN_NORMAL);
99}
